[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ben Hooper bids to be first person to swim the Atlantic

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ben Hooper, from Cheltenham, is attempting to become the first person to officially swim the Atlantic.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
13 November 2016 Last updated at 16:53 GMT
The 38-year-old has set off from Dakar in Senegal to swim to Natal in Brazil. He's hoping to raise Â£1m for charity and to finish the challenge in March.
Other people have attempted the swim but were not ratified by Guinness World Records.
